### Task-Type Routing Map

Use this table to decide which references each agent loads beyond `AGENTS.md` Read First. The orchestrator picks the task tag and surfaces it in the Task Assignment so subagents can short-circuit. See [`references/handoff.md`](plugins/agents-system-setup/skills/agents-system-setup/references/handoff.md#recommended-packet-form) for the per-tag Recommended Packet Form (short-form vs full-form).

| Task tag | Always load | Load when applicable | Safe to skip | Recommended packet form |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `read-only-research` | Read First, Directory Architecture | Topology if topology questions | Security & Audit detail, Threat Model long rationale | short-form |
| `code-edit` | Read First, Directory Architecture, owning agent boundary | Quality Gates row for this path | Marketplace research, full platform schemas | short-form (≤2 files) · full-form when >2 files or shared boundary |
| `security-write` | Security & Audit Matrix, Threat Model, owning agent boundary | Security/Audit reference rows for the change | Long marketplace candidate research | full-form |
| `mcp-write` | MCP approval gate, Security & Audit Matrix | Plugin/MCP rendering reference | Architecture Decisions detail | full-form |
| `replication` | Replication contract, Plan Handoff Contract, Output Contract | Models reference for explicit overrides | Project-specific quality gate detail | full-form |
| `release` | Quality Gates, manifests, version sync rules | Runtime update audit | Long architecture rationale | full-form |
| `docs-only` | Read First | Quality Gates only if doc CI exists | Security/MCP gates unless docs touch credentials | short-form |
| `bug-fix` | Read First, Directory Architecture, owning agent boundary | Quality Gates row, repro logs, related ADRs | Long marketplace research | full-form (Reproduction block required) |
| `learning-check` | Memory & Learning System, Learning Index | Detailed learning entry when category/path matches | Full operational ledger, unrelated learnings | short-form |

### Context Freshness

If `AGENTS.md` was already loaded this turn, prefer `Context freshness: recent` in delegated packets so subagents skip the row-by-row reload and read only the rows for the current task tag.

## Directory Architecture

> **Read this before editing.** Every subagent has a defined ownership zone. Editing outside your zone requires delegating to the owning agent via the orchestrator.

| Path (glob) | Purpose | Owner agent | Edit rule |
|---|---|---|---|
{{DIRECTORY_ARCHITECTURE_ROWS}}

**Rules:**
- `read-only` — agent may read for context, must never write.
- `owned` — agent is the sole writer; others must delegate.
- `additive-only` — agent may append/create but not modify existing entries.
- `shared` — multiple owners; coordinate via orchestrator before edits.

